com.camerontec.util.data

Class SafeBufferOnByteBuffer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.data.AbstractBuffer
      • com.camerontec.util.data.AbstractSafeBuffer
        • com.camerontec.util.data.SafeBufferOnByteBuffer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Buffer, BufferOnByteBuffer

    public final class SafeBufferOnByteBuffer
extends AbstractSafeBuffer
implements BufferOnByteBuffer
    A Buffer implementation which uses a java.nio.ByteBuffer as its backing store.

    Some differences between using this class and a java.nio.ByteBuffer directly are:

    • Range checking is performed but operations guarantee not to throw exceptions when there would otherwise by out of range, underflow or overflow conditions. Please consider whether this is useful in your situation or not.
    • The internal java.nio.ByteBuffer concepts of position and limit are effectively ignored. That is, operations that might fail if performed directly on a java.nio.ByteBuffer can work here. Also, operations guarantee not to affect the value of either position or limit
    • Provided the use case permits, an instance of this class may be replaced by an instance of UnsafeBuffer (they are both Buffers) which can yield significant performance gains in some cases.

    This class is not thread safe.
